parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the key to get stuck, the vehicle to start without a key, or the electrical system to malfunction, leading to safety hazards and potential accidents.
symptoms: Key gets stuck in the ignition switch
vehicle can be started without a key
electrical system malfunctions
horn fails or goes off continuously
smoke appears from the dash panel
and burning smell of electrical components or wire insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause intermittent discharge of the battery, electrical components to burn, and the horn to fail or go off continuously, leading to safety hazards and potential accidents.
symptoms: Intermittent discharge of the battery
electrical components burn
horn fails or goes off continuously
smoke appears from the dash panel
and burning smell of electrical components or wire insulation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of dealerships to repair recalled vehicles can lead to continued safety hazards and potential accidents.
symptoms: Dealerships fail to repair recalled vehicles
parts are not available
or repairs are not made in a timely manner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the aluminum wheel rim can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cracks on the aluminum wheel rim spokes
wheel rim failure
loss of wheel
and potential loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine light being on can indicate a serious problem with the engine, which can lead to engine failure, stalling, or other safety issues.
symptoms: Engine light is on
unknown engine problem
difficulty diagnosing the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven tire wear can cause loss of traction, accidents, and potentially result in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Left front tire wears out more quickly than the other three
despite regular balancing and new tires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case can cause loud noises, vibrations, and difficulty shifting gears, leading to loss of vehicle control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Loud noise when driving
difficulty shifting gears
vehicle will not run properly
loud bang or clunking noise when shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause difficulty shifting gears, loss of power, and sudden jerking or stalling of the vehicle, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or hesitation
difficulty shifting gears
sudden jerking or stalling of the vehicle
feeling like the transmission is trying to lock in two gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to address recall issues related to the power train can lead to continued problems with the transmission and transfer case, causing safety risks and financial burdens for vehicle owners.
symptoms: Vehicle not included in recall despite experiencing similar problems
dealer refusal to help with repair issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the accelerator cable can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the throttle gets stuck
the engine revs very high
the vehicle takes off on its own
the rear tires spin
and the vehicle does not respond to attempts to disengage the throttle or cruise control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the throttle gets stuck
the engine revs very high
the vehicle takes off on its own
and the vehicle does not respond to attempts to disengage the throttle or cruise control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sticking of the throttle linkage can cause unintended acceleration, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The throttle pedal feels stuck
the engine revs very high
and the vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably.
